definition.value: This is an AE which is a mood disorder characterized by periods of depression and periods of abnormally-elevated mood that last from days to weeks each.
This is an AE which is a bipolar spectrum disorder characterized by at least one episode of hypomania and at least one episode of major depression.
This is an AE which is a type of bipolar spectrum disorder characterized by the occurrence of at least one manic episode, with or without mixed or psychotic features.
This is an AE which is a condition of abnormally deep sleep or a stupor from which it is difficult to rouse.
This is an AE which is the cumulative effect of not getting enough sleep.

label.value: irregular sleep wake rhythm disorder AE

definition.value: This is an AE which is a rare form of circadian rhythm sleep disorder.
This is an AE which is a state, during waking up or falling asleep, in which a person is aware but unable to move or speak.
This is an AE which is a broad classification of sleeping disorders involving difficulty getting to sleep, remaining asleep, or of excessive sleepiness.
This is an AE which is characterized by reduced exercise capacity.
This is an AE which refers a chronic condition due to mental or physical impairments arising before adulthood.
This is an AE which is a mental disorder characterized by continuous or relapsing episodes of psychosis.

This is an AE which is a mental disorder diagnosed when symptoms of schizophrenia are present for a significant portion of time (at least a month), but signs of disturbance are not present for the full six months required for the diagnosis of schizophrenia.

This is an AE which is classified as “partial awakenings in which the state of consciousness remains impaired for several minutes without any accompanying major behavioural disorders or severe autonomic responses”.
This is an AE which is an organically caused decline from a previous baseline mental functioning, that develops over a short period of time, typically hours to days.
This is an AE which is a behavioral or mental pattern that causes significant distress or impairment of personal functioning.
This is an AE which is a temporary inability to maintain optimal cognitive performance.

This is an AE which is characterized by backward disequilibrium in a sitting and standing position, reactional hypertonia, an alteration of postural reactions, gait modifications, and fear of falling.

This is an AE which is a chronic disorder of the nervous system characterized by recurrent, unprovoked focal seizures that originate in the temporal lobe of the brain and last about one or two minutes.
This is an AE which is a generalized neurodevelopmental disorder characterized by significantly impaired intellectual and adaptive functioning.
This is an AE which is an abnormal condition of the mind that results in difficulties determining what is real and what is not real.
This is an AE which is the action of violently shaking one's head in rhythm with music.
This is an Ae which is a cutaneous fungal infection (dermatophytosis) of the scalp.
This is an AE which may be a clinical manifestation of autonomic nervous system dysregulation.
This is an AE which is characterized by having difficulty returning to sleep after waking up during the night or very early in the morning.
This is an AE which is a state of tiredness, weariness, fatigue, or lack of energy.

This is an AE which is a rare neurodegenerative disorder characterized by autonomic dysfunction, tremors, slow movement, muscle rigidity, and postural instability (collectively known as parkinsonism) and ataxia.
This is an AE which encompasses several types of dementia involving the frontal and temporal lobes.[3] FTDs are broadly presented as behavioral or language disorders.

This is an AE which is an anxiety disorder in which an individual experiences excessive anxiety regarding separation from home and/or from people to whom the individual has a strong emotional attachment (e.g., a parent, caregiver, significant other, or siblings).
This is an AE which is a neurological examination finding elicited by a reflex test which can help verify the presence or absence of issues arising from the corticospinal tract.
This is an AE which is a type of dementia characterized by changes in sleep, behavior, cognition, movement, and regulation of automatic bodily functions.
This is an AE which is a disorder of the central nervous system.
This is an AE which is a common neurodevelopmental disorder that begins in childhood or adolescence.
This is an AE which is a disease characterized by a weeks-long course of thunderclap headaches, sometimes focal neurologic signs, and occasionally seizures.
This is an AE which is a Gram-negative bacterium that can cause meningitis and other forms of meningococcal disease with bacteraemia.
This is an AE which is a Gram-negative bacterium that can cause meningitis and other forms of meningococcal disease with carditis.
This is an AE which is a medical condition in which poor spinal  blood flow to the brain causes cell death.
This is an AE which is a neurological condition in which the cerebellum is smaller than usual or not completely developed.
This is an AE which is a perceptual disturbance experienced by some with epilepsy or migraine.
This is an AE which is a rare form of chronic, progressive brain inflammation caused by slow infection with certain defective strains of hypermutated measles virus.

This is an AE which is a relatively frequent occurrence in significant head trauma, and their detection is important, as even linear nondisplaced fractures can be associated with critical complications.

This is an AE which is achieved in this model by injecting particles like blood clots (thrombembolic MCAO) or artificial spheres into the carotid artery of animals as an animal model of ischemic stroke.
This is an AE which is an abnormal narrowing in a cerebrovascular  blood vessel or other tubular organ or structure such as foramina and canals.
This is an AE which is an acute inflammation of the protective membranes covering the brain and spinal cord caused by staphylococcal.
This is an AE which is an important and common complication of chimeric antigen receptor-T cell therapies.
This is an AE which is associated with infectious complications, whereas emerging treatments, including anakinra and tocilizumab, may also result in increased susceptibility to certain infections.
